page.title: 05ECOLOGY
page.content: Along the river banks grow hazel,alder,and willow trees.The River Teith is famous for its{trout and {salmon}fishing.Ducks,swans,herons and kingfishers feed on the minnows,sticklebacks,frogs and insect larvae.Above the water you can see dragonflies,mayflies and midges.In the woods,roe deer and squirrels eat the acorns,hazelnuts and beechnuts.Jays, wood pigeons,owls and crows nest among the trees.In the gardens there are robins,blackbirds,starlings,sparrows, thrushes,finches and bluetits.Swallows and martins nest in summer. On open grazing land curlews,snipe,lapwings,larks and oyster catcher nest.Rabbits,hares,mice voles and shrews live here.Dotted around are whin and broom.Wild orchid,globe flower grow in marshy ground.
